"Elderberries are the fruits of a flowering tree called Sambucus, but the plant is more commonly called elder or elderberry. Both the ripe berries and flowers of elderberry plants are used to make elderberry supplements and health tonics, but other parts of the elderberry plant (leaves, roots, seeds and stems) are toxic!

Elderberry has a strong evidence supporting its immune-boosting and antiviral benefits. It is highly recommended if you have upper respiratory symptoms related to the cold and flu! It reduces symptoms of sinus infection and cough! If taken within the first couple of days of feeling sick, it is very effective in shortening the duration of the cold or the flu!

AD  @wisewomanherbals has one of the best elderberry syrups and I highly recommend them if you are looking to keep one in hand! 
It prevents cold and flu, boosts the immune system, reduces symptoms if you’re already sick or have allergy symptoms and TASTES great!...

If you think you have what is going around, or tested positive, I would stay away from it, as we do not know a lot about the new virus and how this herb would interact!"
